  "summary": "Mrs. Ariadne Oliver, a famous mystery novelist, discusses a dog named Ben with Deirdre (Dilly) Henderson. Deirdre recognizes Mrs. Oliver and expresses her admiration for her books, though she notes her mother dislikes detective stories. They discuss a recent murder in a nearby cottage involving an old cleaning lady. Deirdre explains that the victim's tenant, James Bentley, was arrested because she had money hidden under the floor. Deirdre expresses a strong belief in Bentley's innocence, noting that he is a lonely man who recently lost his mother. She mentions that she empathizes with him because she and her mother depend on each other, whereas she has a difficult relationship with her \"heartless\" stepfather, Mr. Weatherby. After Deirdre leaves for Hunter Manor, Mrs. Oliver writes in her notebook that Deirdre is not the killer.\n\nOn her way to the Long Grass Hotel, Mrs. Oliver meets Robin Upward and Eve Carpenter, whose husband is a future MP. Robin jokingly suggests that Mrs. Oliver's next murder scene should take place in Broadhurst Gardens and discusses fictional murder plots involving Eve or himself. Robin also mentions that Eve intends to invite the detective Hercule Poirot to a dinner party at her home. They encounter Molly Samson, who is cleaning a pigsty. Robin introduces Molly to Mrs. Oliver. Eve expresses interest in meeting the tenant, James Bentley, and suggests inviting him to the dinner.",
